Catmandu-FedoraCommons - Perl interface to Fedora Commons using the REST-based API-A,API-M

 use Catmandu::FedoraCommons;
 
 my $fedora = Catmandu::FedoraCommons->new('http://localhost:8080/fedora','fedoraAdmin','fedoraAdmin');

 my $result = $fedora->findObjects(terms=>'*');

 die "error" unless $result->is_ok;

 my $hits = $res->parse_content;

 for my $hit (@{ $hits }) {
    printf "%s\n" , $hit->{pid};
 }

 my $result = $fedora->listDatastreams(pid => 'demo:29')->parse_content;

 $fedora->addDatastream(
                pid => 'demo:29', 
                dsID => 'TEST' , 
                file => 't/marc.xml',
                mimeType => 'text/xml' , 
                controlGroup => 'X');

Status:
-=-=-=-

 This is work in progress. The low level Fedora Commons methods should be working. We are now working 
on a Catmandu::Store implementation of Fedora Commons.
